# Privacy Guard - Cursor AI Rules

## Critical: Read First
ALWAYS read and follow CONVENTIONS.md before making ANY changes.
Path: /home/techtrest/AndroidStudioProjects/PrivacyWidget/CONVENTIONS.md

## Code Generation Standards

### Before Writing Code
1. Read CONVENTIONS.md completely
2. Review similar existing code for patterns
3. Identify potential code duplication
4. Plan extraction of reusable logic

### While Writing Code
- Extract repeated calculations to functions
- Use extension functions for type-specific operations
- Memoize expensive operations with remember(dependencies)
- Never use magic strings or numbers
- Always use MaterialTheme.typography and colorScheme
- Follow Material Design spacing scale (4, 8, 12, 16, 24, 32 dp)

### Kotlin Style Requirements
- Prefer `val` over `var`
- Use `when` expressions over if-else chains
- Data classes must be immutable (no `var`)
- Extension functions for type-specific logic
- Objects for stateless utilities (Calculator, Detector)

### Compose Requirements
- Modifier ALWAYS last parameter with `= Modifier` default
- Composables must be stateless - hoist state up
- Use `remember(key1, key2) { }` with dependencies explicitly listed
- NO business logic in Composables - delegate to Calculators
- Use Material 3 components only (Card, Button, etc.)

### Anti-Patterns to Reject
- ❌ Duplicated calculation logic (extract to function)
- ❌ Magic numbers (extract to const val)
- ❌ Hardcoded colors (#RRGGBB) - use theme
- ❌ Arbitrary fontSize - use MaterialTheme.typography
- ❌ Custom spacing - use Material scale
- ❌ Business logic in Composables
- ❌ Nullable types without reason

### File Organization
- Screens: ui/screens/XxxScreen.kt
- Components: ui/components/XxxComponent.kt
- Models: data/model/Xxx.kt
- Logic: data/scanner/ (Calculator, Detector objects)

### Quality Checks Before Completing
1. No code duplication? (Check for repeated patterns)
2. No magic strings/numbers? (All extracted to constants)
3. Follows naming conventions? (PascalCase, camelCase, UPPER_SNAKE_CASE)
4. Uses theme colors/typography? (No hardcoded values)
5. Proper Modifier usage? (Last param, default value)
6. State properly hoisted? (Composables stateless)
7. Business logic separated? (Not in Composables)

### When Stuck or Unsure
- Review existing similar code in codebase
- Check CONVENTIONS.md for specific guidance
- Ask for clarification rather than guessing
- Suggest refactoring if existing code violates conventions

## Testing Requirements
- Code must build successfully
- No linter warnings
- Test on actual device/emulator when possible
- Verify UI matches Material Design 3

## Project-Specific Rules

### Privacy Philosophy
- Minimal permissions (never request invasive permissions)
- Transparent about limitations
- No tracking or analytics
- F-Droid compatible (no proprietary dependencies)

### Scoring System
- All point deductions defined in PrivacyCheck enum
- Use PrivacyScoreCalculator for calculations
- Never hardcode point values in UI
- Floor score at 0 (no negative scores)

### UI Design
- British Racing Green primary color
- Card-based layouts with 12dp corners, 2dp elevation
- Consistent iconography (Material Icons)
- Professional, clean aesthetic
- No emoji in production UI

## Remember
Code quality matters. Take time to do it right.
Consistency across the codebase is more important than individual cleverness.
When in doubt, follow existing patterns or ask for guidance.
